## Install

Verify the SHA-256 checksum of every downloaded asset against the
`SHA256SUMS` file shipped with this release before installing.

### PyPI — any Linux (needs Python 3.11+)

```sh
pip install --pre ferm==@VER@
```

`@resolve()` with record types beyond `A`/`AAAA` needs the optional extra:

```sh
pip install --pre 'ferm[dns]==@VER@'
```

### Debian / Ubuntu — native `.deb`

```sh
curl -fLO @BASE@/@DEB@
curl -fLO @BASE@/SHA256SUMS
sha256sum --ignore-missing -c SHA256SUMS
sudo apt install ./@DEB@
```

The package installs `/usr/bin/ferm` and a `ferm.service` unit that is **not**
enabled or started on install (anti-lockout). Enable it only after writing
`/etc/ferm/ferm.conf`.

### Fedora / RHEL / Rocky — native `.rpm`

```sh
curl -fLO @BASE@/@RPM@
curl -fLO @BASE@/SHA256SUMS
sha256sum --ignore-missing -c SHA256SUMS
sudo dnf install ./@RPM@
```

A `noarch` package: it installs `/usr/bin/ferm` and a `ferm.service` unit that
is **not** enabled or started on install (anti-lockout). Enable it only after
writing `/etc/ferm/ferm.conf`.

### Alpine — native `.apk`

```sh
curl -fLO @BASE@/@APK@
curl -fLO @BASE@/SHA256SUMS
sha256sum --ignore-missing -c SHA256SUMS
# --allow-untrusted: a manually downloaded .apk is not signed by a
# configured repository key.
sudo apk add --allow-untrusted ./@APK@
```

The package installs `/usr/bin/ferm` and an OpenRC `ferm` service that is
**not** enabled or started on install (anti-lockout). Enable it only after
writing `/etc/ferm/ferm.conf`.

### Standalone binary — Linux x86_64 (glibc 2.28+)

Bundles its own Python runtime; the host needs only `iptables` / `nft`.

```sh
curl -fLO @BASE@/ferm-@VER@-linux-x86_64.tar.gz
curl -fLO @BASE@/SHA256SUMS
sha256sum --ignore-missing -c SHA256SUMS
tar xzf ferm-@VER@-linux-x86_64.tar.gz
# Keep ferm.dist/ intact; link the binary instead of copying it out.
sudo ln -s "$PWD/ferm.dist/ferm" /usr/local/bin/ferm
ferm --version
```

